# Terminal Sink Agent

`mn-agents.control.terminal_sink@1` is the terminal reducer for a
report-producing workflow. Its `terminal_report_sink` stereotype marks the run
complete when the final report message reaches the node.

Place one terminal sink at the end of the DAG and connect the final report edge
to it. Do not use it as an artifact composer; generate and validate artifacts
before sending the terminal message.

## Recommended manifest use

```json
{
  "node_id": "report_sink",
  "role": "result_sink",
  "uses": "mn-agents.control.terminal_sink@1",
  "with": {
    "stereotype": "terminal_report_sink"
  }
}
```

The stereotype expands to:

```json
{
  "complete_on_message": true,
  "complete_run": true,
  "terminal_sink": true
}
```

The rendered node is an `aggregator` with `type="reduce"` and the supplied
role.

## Message boundary

Behavior metadata declares a `blueprint_report` input transition and a
`run_completed` output. The transition terminates with reason
`terminal_report_received`.

Keep this boundary stable when refactoring a workflow. Moving completion into
an earlier worker can mark incomplete artifacts as successful and bypass human
review or final quality checks.

## Overrides

Optional `with` fields include `complete_on_message`, `complete_run`,
`terminal_sink`, `output_message_type`, `role`, and `node_type`. Explicit
instance values override stereotype values; explicit top-level `config`
overrides rendered config last.

See [SPEC.md](SPEC.md) for the normative rendering and lifecycle contract.
